{
  "info": {
    "name": "ScanPet Mobile Backend API v4",
    "description": "Complete API collection for ScanPet Mobile Backend v4.\n\nChanges in v4 (latest):\n- Orders: Now tied to Inventory (not Location). POST /api/orders body uses `inventoryId`\n- Users: Default inventories are now an ARRAY (`defaultInventoryIds` / `defaultInventoryNames`)\n- Users: Default locations are now supported as an ARRAY (`defaultLocationIds` / `defaultLocationNames`)\n- Auth: Register body accepts `defaultInventoryIds` and `defaultLocationIds` arrays\n- Users: POST /api/users and responses include arrays for both defaults\n- Users: NEW endpoint PUT /api/users/{id}/default-locations to set the full list of default locations\n- Users: PUT /api/users/{id}/default-inventory now takes `defaultInventoryIds` array (replaces full list)\n- Auth: /me, login, and refresh responses include both default inventories and default locations arrays\n- Inventories: NEW endpoint GET /api/inventories/item-counts returns totals per item per inventory\n- Inventories: NEW endpoint GET /api/inventories/{inventoryId}/item-counts for a single inventory\n\nChanges in v3:\n- Images on Cloudinary CDN, RGB/SKU uniqueness, partial refunds, OrderItemStatus\n\nDefault credentials:\n- Admin: admin / Admin@123\n- Manager: manager / Manager@123\n- User: user / User@123",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "https://scanpet-production.up.railway.app", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "refreshToken", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "userId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "roleId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "colorId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "itemId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "locationId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "orderId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "inventoryId", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
